criteria.textblock:
        Inclusion Criteria:

          -  Patients or their families complain of significant memory impairment;

          -  Objective memory impairment (e.g., tests of article identification, recall, delayed
             memory);

          -  Be able to obtain complete diagnosis and treatment records and be able to carry out
             long-term follow-up;

          -  Signed written consent.

        Exclusion Criteria:

          -  Psychiatric disorders: including anxiety disorder, affective disorder, severe
             psychosis, or drug-induced psychosis;

          -  Pregnancy or lactation.
